# Steering — Test strategy (cross-cutting, agent-wide)

## Layered pyramid

- Unit tests cover individual functions. Required for every public method.
- Integration tests cover module-to-module interactions (DB, queue, HTTP boundary).
- Acceptance tests (Gherkin in `acceptance/*.feature`) cover requirement-level behaviour mapped to REQ-NNN.

## Coverage targets

- Unit: NN% per package (CI enforces)
- Integration: every feature exercised end-to-end at least once
- Acceptance: every REQ-NNN has at least one Gherkin scenario

## Test data

- Fixtures live under `tests/fixtures/<feature>/`
- No production data in test fixtures
- Synthetic data generation uses `faker` / equivalent (NEVER copy real user data)

## CI gates

- Lint must pass (PROJECT.json#lint_command)
- Tests must pass (PROJECT.json#test_command)
- Coverage must meet thresholds
- High-severity static-analysis findings block merge

## Agent-specific

- Workers that delete or disable tests to make CI green VIOLATE Article I of constitution.md
- Merge-coordinator's lint+test gate catches this — patches that delete tests fail the lint step
